.PP
.B grafana-util status snapshot [\fISUBCOMMAND\fR] [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
grafana-util is a command-line interface for reviewing Grafana changes with live inventory, diff, preview, and safe apply workflows in one executable and one namespaced command shape.
.PP
Use this page as a router: pick the namespace first, then open the namespace or subcommand manpage for detailed options and examples.
.SH TOP-LEVEL COMMANDS
Each entry below is a command family, not the full workflow reference.
.TP
.B dashboard
Dashboard workflows: browse, export, import, review, diff, edit, publish, and capture. See grafana\-util\-dashboard(1).
.TP
.B alert
Alerting workflows: export, import, diff, plan, apply, delete, list, and author alert resources. See grafana\-util\-alert(1).
.TP
.B datasource
Datasource workflows: list, browse, export, import, diff, create, modify, delete, and inspect supported types. See grafana\-util\-datasource(1).
.TP
.B access
Access workflows: manage users, orgs, teams, service accounts, and service\-account tokens. See grafana\-util\-access(1).
.TP
.B config
Configuration workflows: create, inspect, validate, and reuse repo\-local connection profiles. See grafana\-util\-config(1).
.TP
.B status
Read\-only status workflows: live readiness, staged checks, overviews, snapshots, and generic resource reads. See grafana\-util\-status(1).
.TP
.B workspace
Workspace workflows: scan, test, preview, package, and apply one local Grafana workspace. See grafana\-util\-workspace(1).
.TP
.B status snapshot
Snapshot workflows: export and review local dashboard and datasource inventory bundles. See grafana\-util\-status\-snapshot(1).
